ity amplitude for\nhigh-luminosity AGNs, but as the luminosity drops to $\\lesssim 10^{42}$ erg\ns$^{-1}$, the variability amplitude no longer appears dependent on the\nluminosity. The entire observed luminosity-variability trend can be roughly\nreproduced by an empirical AGN variability model based on a broken power-law\npower spectral density function.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Oct 2018 18:00:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-05"}
