ting observations with the IRAM 30m\ntelescope, we find that 6 cores show blue-skewed profile, while 4 cores show\nred-skewed profile. [$\\rm {HCO}^{+}$]/[HNC] and [$\\rm {HCO}^{+}$]/$\\rm\n[N_{2}H^{+}]$ in protostellar cores are higher than those in prestellar cores;\nthis can be used as chemical clocks. The best-fit chemical age of the cores\nwith line observations is $\\sim 5\\times 10^4$~years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Oct 2018 20:00:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Oct 2018 17:56:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 12 Mar 2019 16:03:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-13"}
